<h5>Commonalities</h5>

<p>All the demos rely upon the jQuery validation plugin and share the same initialisation code below.  By the way, the <code>errorPlacement</code> option is only in place so that radio validations are styled a little better.</p>

<pre class="prettyprint js">
  var $form = $("form");
  $form.validate({
      errorPlacement: function($errorLabel, $element) {

          var $elementToInsertAfter = $element;
          if ($element.prop("type") === "radio") {
              $elementToInsertAfter = $element.closest(".controls");
          } 
      
          $errorLabel.insertAfter($elementToInsertAfter);
      },

      submitHandler: function (form) {
          alert("This is a valid form!");
      }
  });
</pre>
